This paper proposes a stochastic optimization method for machine learning problems, which is likely to fall under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the convergence properties of the proposed method, which involves numerical analysis and optimization, making it relevant to "Numerical Analysis" (cs.NA) and "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper applies the proposed method to various machine learning problems, including empirical risk minimization and leading eigenvalue computation, indicating its relevance to "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) sub-categories.
